etymologies: late 16th century: from Spanish or Portuguese rosca ‘twist, coil, roll of bread’, of unknown ultimate origin

definitions: a light, dry biscuit or piece of twice-baked bread, especially one prepared for use as baby food.
shortDefinitions: light, dry biscuit or piece of twice-baked bread

definitions: twice-baked bread used as extra filling, for example in sausages, and formerly as rations at sea.
shortDefinitions: twice-baked bread used in foods such as sausages
